SIMPLE: willful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Willful
<hw>Will"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Will</ets> +
<ets>full</ets>.]</ety> <ety>[Written also <ets>wilful</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of set purpose; self-determined; voluntary; <as>as,
<ex>willful</ex> murder</as>.</def> <rj><au>Foxe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In <qex>willful poverty chose to lead his life</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou to me⟦br⟧
Art all things under heaven, all places thou,⟦br⟧
Who, for my <qex>willful</qex> crime, art banished hence.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Governed by the will without yielding to reason;
obstinate; perverse; inflexible; stubborn; refractory; <as>as, a
<ex>willful</ex> man or horse</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Will"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Will"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Willier</ent>⟦br⟧
